   Water Resources of New Hampshire and Vermont
   Outreach & Education

   USGS Sites:
     * NH/VT District
          + Contoocook River stream-gaging outreach and educational site
          + Water-Use in New Hampshire and Vermont :Activity Guide for
            Teachers (Watershed map included)
     * National
          + Water Science for Schools (Information on many aspects of
            water, along with pictures, data, maps, and an interactive
            center where you can give opinions and test your water
            knowledge.)
          + Learning Web (Web site dedicated to K-12 education,
            exploration, and life-long learning.)
          + Mapping-related teacher resources online (USGS Educational
            Resources for Cartography, Geography, and Related Disciplines)
          + Geo Center (Geoscience Education Outreach Center, a special
            resource area for USGS personnel and teachers involved in
            earth science instruction for grades K-12.)
          + USGS Whooping Crane award-winning web site

   Other Sites:
     * New Hampshire Consortium on Arsenic
     * New Hampshire Project WET (Water Education for Teachers)
     * Vermont Project WET (Water Education for Teachers)
     * National Science Teachers Association
     * Terraweb (Topographic Maps Online)

